# Vercel Speed Insights Implementation

## Summary
Successfully implemented Vercel Speed Insights in the EventX Studio frontend application following the official Vercel documentation for React applications.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Added `@vercel/speed-insights` package (v1.3.1) to the project dependencies
- Updated `package.json` and `pnpm-lock.yaml` with the new package

### 2. SpeedInsights Component Integration
- Modified `src/App.jsx` to integrate Speed Insights tracking
- Added import statement: `import { SpeedInsights } from '@vercel/speed-insights/react';`
- Added `<SpeedInsights />` component to the main App component, wrapped inside the ErrorBoundary for proper error handling

### Implementation Details

The SpeedInsights component was placed inside the App function component, after the AppContent component but still within the ErrorBoundary wrapper. This ensures:

1. **Global Coverage**: Speed Insights will track performance across all routes and pages
2. **Error Handling**: The component is protected by the ErrorBoundary
3. **Minimal Intrusion**: The implementation follows React best practices and doesn't affect existing functionality

### Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/speed-insights dependency
- `pnpm-lock.yaml` - Updated lockfile with new package and its dependencies
- `src/App.jsx` - Added SpeedInsights import and component

### Build Verification
✅ Build completed successfully (7.41s)
✅ No new linting errors introduced
✅ Bundle size: 1,749.65 kB (494.33 kB gzipped)

## Next Steps for Deployment

To complete the Speed Insights setup:

1. **Enable Speed Insights in Vercel Dashboard**
   - Go to the Vercel dashboard
   - Select the EventX Studio project
   - Navigate to the Speed Insights tab
   - Click "Enable"

2. **Deploy to Vercel**
   - Run `vercel deploy` or push to the connected git repository
   - Vercel will automatically add the `/_vercel/speed-insights/*` routes

3. **Verify Installation**
   - After deployment, check the page source
   - Look for the `/_vercel/speed-insights/script.js` script in the body tag

4. **View Metrics**
   - Visit the Vercel dashboard after deployment
   - Select the project and click the Speed Insights tab
   - Metrics will appear after users visit the site

## Technical Notes

- The implementation uses `@vercel/speed-insights/react` which provides seamless React integration
- The component is lightweight and automatically tracks Core Web Vitals metrics
- No additional configuration is required for basic functionality
- The tracking script only runs on Vercel deployments (no impact on local development)
